verrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior spans authorization/policy check plus audit-record persistence, which is module interaction beyond unit scope. Rejected System because text only requires an \"auditable warning record\" and does not require proving visibility in an external system/API. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no LLM decision quality or multi-agent chain is involved.","test_description":"Invoke manual override path with and without override flag through application service; assert rejection without flag and persisted warning record when override is allowed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is state/metadata handoff (fix commit marker vs review-round metadata) across modules. Integration is the lowest level that validates ordering check end-to-end in-app. Rejected System: behavior text does not require real git subprocess semantics, only that identifier is \"produced after\" latest fix commit; this can be validated with persisted commit/round metadata. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: no requirement to validate model output quality or multiple agentic decisions.","test_description":"Seed fix-commit metadata and review-round metadata in local store, then run gate finalization logic; assert PASS blocked when review round predates latest fix and allowed only when round is newer.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on a real review-agent round in live flow; a stub can falsely satisfy \"round ran\" without validating real agent execution on updated diff context. Agentic is required because execution path passes through a real AI review call. Rejected Workflow because this behavior can be validated with a single required fresh agent round gate before PASS, not necessarily multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run live loop with an actual review-agent call after a diff update; assert PASS finalization remains blocked until a new post-fix agent round is recorded from that real run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.23}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Decision is deterministic policy over stored findings + round budget, requiring repo/service wiring but not real OS/network/model behavior. Rejected Workflow because behavior text focuses on \"stored results\" at exhaustion state, not executing the multi-round loop itself. Rejected Agentic since correctness is not model-output quality-dependent here.","test_description":"Populate stored results with unresolved MUST-FIX and max-rounds reached, execute outcome computation through app layer, and assert escalation is returned instead of PASS.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.17}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires live multi-round sequencing and final decision after exhaustion, so single-step tests can miss cross-round handoff/regression. Workflow is needed to validate end-to-end pipeline behavior across rounds and final escalation emission. Rejected Agentic-only because the key risk is sequence correctness across multiple rounds, not one model call. Rejected System-only because infra realism alone does not cover multi-step policy progression.","test_description":"Execute a full live multi-round review pipeline until round budget is exhausted while unresolved MUST-FIX persists; assert PASS remains blocked and escalation event/verdict is emitted at workflow end.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.64}}]}
